text: Südheide is a municipality in Celle, in Lower Saxony, Germany. It takes its name from the heathland Südheide. It was formed on 1 January 2015 by the merger of the previous municipalities Hermannsburg and Unterlüß. The villages of Südheide are: Baven, Beckedorf, Bonstorf, Hermannsburg, Lutterloh, Oldendorf, Unterlüß, Weesen. ==References== Category:Celle (district)
